Dear John K. Johnstone,

Thank you for your submission to ACMSE 2003.  We are pleased to inform 
you that your paper, titled

"Kernels from hulls"

has been accepted as for publication in the Proceedings.
Papers went through a rigorous reviewing process.  Each paper was
reviewed by at least two of the 58 reviewers. Of the 133 papers 
submitted, a total of 100 full, short, and student papers were accepted.

Please carefully take into account the enclosed comments by the 
reviewers when preparing the camera-ready version. It is incumbent 
upon you to do so.

Full papers are limited to 6 pages and short/position papers to 
2 pages.  Your camera-ready paper is due on February 3, 2002.  
Adherence to the alternate style for ACM SIG proceedings 
http://www.acm.org/sigs/pubs/proceed/template.html, is necessary 
for the publication of your paper.

To submit your paper, revisit the ACMSE 2003 submission site at
http://vision.armstrong.edu/acmse/, go to step 3, and use the 
following login name and password to submit your file:

Login: jj@cis.uab.edu
Password: E00-1182831445

You will need to submit both a file containing your document source(s) 
and a final file in pdf or postscript format.

At least one author is required to register for the conference at
http://vision.armstrong.edu/acmse/registration.html before
Monday, February 10th; if this is a problem, please notify us 
**immediately**.

Congratulations on having your paper accepted. We look forward to 
seeing you in Savannah.

Sincerely,

Dr. Mark Burge
ACMSE 2003 PC Chair
